<h1 style="font-size:clamp(24px,4vw,38px);font-weight:400;color:#fff;margin:16px 0;line-height:1.2;">What is a smart health ring for — and do you actually need one</h1>
<p style="font-size:17px;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.55);margin-bottom:8px;">A smart ring is a health sensor you wear on your finger. It measures your sleep, heart rate and activity 24 hours a day, without a screen and without you even noticing it.</p>
<div style="font-size:11px;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.3);font-family:monospace;margin-bottom:28px;">📅 May 2026 · ⏱ 7 min read</div>
<img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1576566588028-4147f3842f27?w=800&q=80" alt="Smart health ring" style="width:100%;border-radius:12px;aspect-ratio:16/9;object-fit:cover;margin-bottom:28px;" loading="lazy"/>
<div class="verdict-box">
  <span class="verdict-box__label">⚡ QUICK CONCLUSION</span>
  <p>If you struggle to sleep well, want to understand your recovery, or are looking for health data without wearing a watch on your wrist, a smart ring can change how you understand your body. If you just want to count steps, you don't need one.</p>
