<div class="article-content">
<h2>What exactly is a smart ring?</h2>
<img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1434494878577-86c23bcb06b9?w=800&q=80" alt="Wearable health technology" style="width:100%;border-radius:10px;aspect-ratio:16/9;object-fit:cover;margin-bottom:20px;" loading="lazy"/>
<p>A smart ring is a wearable the size of a jewelry ring with optical sensors inside. Those sensors constantly measure your heart rate, body temperature, heart rate variability (HRV) and movement.</p>
<p>The key difference from a smartwatch is that it has no screen. All information is processed in the phone app. This has a huge advantage: you can wear it while sleeping without discomfort, in the shower, at the gym or in a meeting without anyone noticing.</p>
