<h2>What a smart ring measures</h2>
<img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1559757148-5c350d0d3c56?w=800&q=80" alt="Health monitoring data" style="width:100%;border-radius:10px;aspect-ratio:16/9;object-fit:cover;margin-bottom:20px;" loading="lazy"/>
<p><strong>Sleep:</strong> This is where rings truly shine. They measure sleep stages (light, deep, REM), interruptions and overall quality.</p>
<p><strong>Resting heart rate:</strong> A key indicator of your recovery state. If it rises several days in a row, your body needs rest.</p>
<p><strong>HRV (Heart Rate Variability):</strong> The most advanced metric. A high HRV indicates good recovery; a low one suggests stress or fatigue.</p>
<p><strong>Body temperature:</strong> Very useful for detecting if you're coming down with something or for menstrual cycle tracking.</p>
<h2>Is a smart ring worth it in 2026?</h2>
<p><strong>Yes, it's worth it if:</strong> you have sleep problems, you exercise and want to optimize your recovery, or you dislike wearing a watch on your wrist.</p>
<p><strong>It's not worth it if:</strong> you just want to count steps, you need GPS for running, or you have an iPhone and want the Samsung Galaxy Ring (Android only).</p>
<h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>
<div class="faq-item"><p class="faq-item__q">Is a smart ring the same as a smartwatch?</p><p class="faq-item__a">No. A smart ring has no screen or notifications. Its function is exclusively passive health tracking. A smartwatch does more things but is less comfortable to sleep in and has less battery.</p></div>
<div class="faq-item"><p class="faq-item__q">How long does a smart ring battery last?</p><p class="faq-item__a">Between 6 and 10 days depending on the model. Oura Ring 4 lasts about 8 days, Samsung Galaxy Ring about 7, and RingConn Gen 2 Air reaches 10 days.</p></div>
<div class="faq-item"><p class="faq-item__q">Can you use it in the shower and while exercising?</p><p class="faq-item__a">Yes. All main models have IP68 protection. You can shower, swim and do any sport without removing it.</p></div>
<div class="faq-item"><p class="faq-item__q">Does the Oura Ring need a monthly subscription?</p><p class="faq-item__a">Yes. Oura Ring costs about $349 plus a $6/month subscription for full analytics. Samsung Galaxy Ring and Ultrahuman require no subscription.</p></div>
<div class="faq-item"><p class="faq-item__q">Does it work with iPhone?</p><p class="faq-item__a">Depends on the model. Oura Ring and Ultrahuman have apps for iOS and Android. Samsung Galaxy Ring only works with Android.</p></div>
<div class="faq-item"><p class="faq-item__q">Where to buy in the US?</p><p class="faq-item__a">Oura Ring at ouraring.com and Best Buy. Samsung Galaxy Ring at samsung.com/us, Best Buy and Amazon. Ultrahuman at ultrahuman.com.</p></div>
</div>
